properties.areaDesc: West Slopes South Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Central Cascades and Passes; West Slopes North Cascades and Passes
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 6 at 10:05AM PST until February 7 at 1:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow continued above 4000 feet. Additional snow
accumulations up to 11 inches.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains and valleys of Whatcom and Skagit
Counties, including the Mount Baker Ski Area, Cascade mountains
and valleys of Snohomish and King Counties, including Stevens
Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass and Cascade mountains and valleys of
Pierce and Lewis Counties, including the Crystal Mountain Ski
Area, Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...Until 1 AM PST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow levels today will fluctuate from 4,000
to 6,000 feet, with the higher snow levels across the Cascades
of Lewis and Pierce Counties. Rain/snow mix at times for
Snoqualmie Pass. Very dangerous avalanche conditions will exist
in many areas into tonight. Travel in avalanche terrain is not
recommended.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 1 AM PST FRIDAY ABOVE 4000 FEET
